H0.text: Organs are structures in multicellular organisms that carry out essential biological functions.

H1.text: Atoms carry out essential biological functions in multicellular organisms.

H2.text: Cells carry out essential biological functions in multicellular organisms.

H3.text: Molecules carry out essential biological functions in multicellular organisms.

A4.text: The cell is the basic structural and functional unit of all forms of life or organisms.

A5.text: Prokaryotic cells were likely the first form of life on Earth, characterized by having vital biological processes including cell signaling.
